{"title":"Lightning (monster spell)","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Lightning_(monster_spell)","type":"markdown","data":"- *This article is about the [monster spell](/wiki/Monster_spell \"Monster spell\"). For other similarly-named pages, see [Lightning](/wiki/Lightning \"Lightning\").*\n\n**Lightning** is a [monster spell](/wiki/Monster_spell \"Monster spell\") in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")* that is used by some of the stronger [clerical spell](/wiki/Clerical_spell \"Clerical spell\") casters.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Description](#Description)\n- [2 Messages](#Messages)\n- [3 History](#History)\n- [4 Variants](#Variants)\n  - [4.1 EvilHack](#EvilHack)\n- [5 References](#References)\n\n## Description\n\nLightning can be used by any monster that can cast clerical spells and is at least [level](/wiki/Monster_level \"Monster level\") 12. When cast, a bolt of [lightning](/wiki/Lightning \"Lightning\") strikes the [player](/wiki/Player \"Player\") character from above and deals 8d6 [shock](/wiki/Shock \"Shock\") damage, destroying [wands](/wiki/Wand \"Wand\") and [rings](/wiki/Ring \"Ring\") in open inventory, and [blinds](/wiki/Blind \"Blind\") you for up to 100 turns regardless of damage.[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2) The bolt's damage can be reduced by [half spell damage](/wiki/Half_spell_damage \"Half spell damage\"), and [shock resistance](/wiki/Shock_resistance \"Shock resistance\") and [reflection](/wiki/Reflection \"Reflection\") prevent damage completely.[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3)[\\[4\\]](#cite_note-4)\n\n*The following information pertains to an upcoming version ([3.7.0](/wiki/3.7.0 \"3.7.0\")). If this version is now released, please verify that it is still accurate, then update the page to incorporate this information.*\n\nPer [commit 6b8079a1](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/commit/6b8079a16f425aa80239b0b1009ec98a70af56ff), the lightning spell will destroy any [iron bars](/wiki/Iron_bars \"Iron bars\") if the character is targeted while occupying their square.\n\n## Messages\n\n- A bolt of lightning strikes down at you from above!\n\n  A monster cast lightning at you.\n\n- It bounces off your \\<amulet/armor/scales/weapon>.\n\n  A source of reflection deflected the spell.\n\n## History\n\nIn [NetHack 3.4.3](/wiki/NetHack_3.4.3 \"NetHack 3.4.3\") and earlier versions, including some variants based on those versions, the lightning monster spell does not cause blindness like other lightning effects; this is [C342-46](/wiki/Bugs_in_NetHack_3.4.3 \"Bugs in NetHack 3.4.3\"), which is corrected in [NetHack 3.6.0](/wiki/NetHack_3.6.0 \"NetHack 3.6.0\") via [commit 7de00a45](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/commit/7de00a45beea2e498f3edf2afa1354d443e25c8e).\n\n## Variants\n\n### EvilHack\n\nIn [EvilHack](/wiki/EvilHack \"EvilHack\"), clerical spellcasting monsters can use the lightning monster spell at level 11, and the spell can be used against other monsters. [Kathryn the Ice Queen](/wiki/Kathryn_the_Ice_Queen \"Kathryn the Ice Queen\") and [Asmodeus](/wiki/Asmodeus \"Asmodeus\") will cast this spell instead of [fire pillar](/wiki/Fire_pillar \"Fire pillar\").\n\nReflection no longer provides complete protection against the spell.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 571](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L571): *damage*\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 576](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L576): *blindness*\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 565](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L565): *damage prevention*\n4. [↑](#cite_ref-4) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 576](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L576): *half spell damage reduction*\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Lightning (monster spell) - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Lightning_(monster_spell)\",\"wgTitle\":\"Lightning (monster spell)\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":160828,\"wgRevisionId\":160828,\"wgArticleId\":14877,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Upcoming\",\"Nethack-367 articles\",\"Monster spells\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Lightning_(monster_spell)\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":14877,\"wgRequestId\":\"4a068d6738e7a6eaec0f49d1\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\"